# YouTube Banner Standards

## Banner Design Requirements

All YouTube banners for video lessons must follow these specifications:

### Dimensions & Format
- **Size**: 2560x1440 pixels (YouTube standard)
- **Format**: PNG
- **Color space**: RGB

### Visual Elements

**Background**:
- Use the library background image (Dmitry Kalashnik with books and Torah scroll)
- Maintain professional, scholarly atmosphere
- Ensure good contrast for text readability

**Styling**:
- White and gold curved border on the left side
- Gold decorative ornaments (crown, floral patterns, dividers)
- Semi-transparent dark overlay behind text areas (for readability)
- Jewish/Hebrew theme elements (Star of David, etc.)

### Text Hierarchy

| Level | Purpose | Style | Color |
|-------|---------|-------|-------|
| Primary | Lesson title/question | Large, elegant serif font | Gold |
| Secondary | Subtitle/source | Medium, elegant serif | White |
| Tertiary | Name plate | "ДМИТРИЙ КАЛАШНИК" | White on dark background |

### File Naming Convention

```
youtube_banner_kalashnik_[descriptive_topic].png
```

Examples:
- `youtube_banner_kalashnik_children_fire.png`
- `youtube_banner_kalashnik_bruki_nosok.png`
- `youtube_banner_kalashnik_znamena.png`

### Consistency Checklist

When creating new banners, verify:

- [ ] Background image is the original library scene
- [ ] Left border styling matches previous banners
- [ ] Gold decorative elements are present and consistent
- [ ] Name plate shows "ДМИТРИЙ КАЛАШНИК"
- [ ] Text is readable and properly positioned
- [ ] Colors match the gold/white/dark scheme
- [ ] Overall professional and scholarly appearance

